Package: RFIF
Type: Package
Title: Fast Iterative Filtering (FIF) with Portable FFT Backend
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chuck", "Coleman", role = c("aut","cre"), email = "cdcoleman113@gmail.com"),
    person("Emanuele", "Papini", role = "ctb"),
    person("Igor", "Bertello", role = "ctb"),
    person("Antonio", "Cicone", role = "ctb")
 )
Description: Provides an R interface to a C implementation of Fast Iterative Filtering (FIF)
    for decomposing a univariate signal into intrinsic mode functions (IMFs) and a residual.
    The package uses FFTW-3, if found.  If not, it provides instructions to install it for
    your OS.  This is recommended, as R's internal fft(), while avoiding external FFT
    dependencies, is two orders of magnitude slower.
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
